description:
Roles & Responsibilities
1. Ensure all Authorities procedures and information are properly documented;
2. Ensure site progress are met in accordance to the master programme;
3. Ensure all the latest details, information, drawings and documents are updated in the office and on site;
4. Drawings, shop drawings preparation in a timely and in accordance to the requirement or instructions of the Manager
5. To ensure documents and drawings are kept both in hard and soft copy and in a timely and proper manner;
6. Track the progress of delivery and quality of materials in accordance with the construction schedule to prevent delays;
7. Assist in the tendering process;
8. Taking off and any calculation as required;
9. Attend meetings and assist with determination of project requirements when requested;
10. Effectively and accurately communicate relevant project information to the client and project team;
11. Ensure clients’ needs are met in a timely and cost effective manner;
12. Understands the project plans, specifications and explain plans and to all general workers, and/or clients when need to;
13. Monitor and control all sub-contractors’ and Project’s programme status;
14. Maintains positive relationships with Client, Architects, Consultants, Authorities, all Contractors, suppliers and any other relevant personnel;
15. Maintains an organized and safe work place;
16. Communicate ideas for improving company processes with a positive and constructive attitude, and for developing this attitude in others;
17. Keep the Project Manager (PM) and others informed about project status and issues that may impact client relations and report to PM daily on-site status;
18. Any other tasks and duties as instructed by the management.

Roles & Responsibilities
Degree or Diploma in Architecture or Civil / Construction Engineering, or formally trained in BIM (Diploma or Modelling Training certification);
At least 3 years of engineering experience in BIM-based construction, design, drafting, coordination, drawing production, submission to the local authority;
Experience in large to a mega large public project, building and infrastructure projects in various regions.
Background in both private sector and developer;
Certification & seminar in term of BIM, VDC and IDD domain.
At least 3 years of BIM coordination and/or BIM management and modelling experience in design, engineering or construction projects; and
Proficient in Autodesk Revit, AutoCAD, SketchUp, Navisworks, ArchiCAD and Bentley BIM Suite etc.

Roles & Responsibilities
Job Description
Responsible for the implementation of Structured Cabling System (Voice/Data/Fiber Optics);
Presales support;
Prepare layout/Shop/Schematic Drawings;
Implement and maintain high quality/safety standards at site;
Perform User Acceptance Test and Handling Over of Projects with Clients & Consultants;
Prepare, compile and maintain proper documentation for all projects;
Attend site meetings & liaise with contractors/consultants;
Co-ordinate, manage resources, personnel & execute project works within the designated time frame.

Requirements
Min GCE "O" level equivalent, ITE or Diploma in Electrical/Mechanical or related fields
Good in computer software especially in Autocad, MS Visio & MS Project
Ability to multi-task
A team-player with pleasant personality and positive mind-set

Roles & Responsibilities
1) Assisting in Coordinating production and assembling of products accordingly;
2) Responsible for inspecting and QC of completed projects/orders before delivery/shipping;
3) Liaising with customers for their projects;
4) managing deadlines and workflow ;
5) Planning of new projects.

Candidates who :
1) have a keen eye for detail and the ability to work with a team ;
2) have problem-solving skills and able to deal with various challenges and issues that may arise during the project, able to identify, analyze, and resolve problems in a timely and effective manner
3) Have the passion to learn new things
~Training will be provided~

Roles & Responsibilities
Responsibility:
- Monitor & supervise team to ensure compliance of work;
- Check the quality, workmanship, ensure all standards are being met and ensure accuracy of the items being produced before items are being delivered, installed or collected;
- Ensure relevant paperwork (Safety, PTW etc) is completed, updated and submitted
- Must be able to read Interior design drawings & detailings;
- Managing a team of subcontractors, suppliers, and other parties involved in the project;
- Provide regular reports to the Management on the progress of overall works in assigned projects;
- May involve some late nights / weekends supervision at our job sites;
-Handle project coordination and responsible for all works in designated projects
-Responsible in overseeing the overall site progress to ensure the structural, architectural and MEP works of the project team and sub-contractors are in compliance to the defined standards and Safety regulations;
-Plan and advise the construction foreman on sequencing and arrangement of work;
-Attend technical meeting/site meetings with consultants, and provide technical solutions;
-Ensure the site works are carried out according to specifications / drawings.

Roles & Responsibilities
The Project Coordinator is responsible for the overall programme schedule, to ensure successful tracking and reporting throughout the project lifecycle, from planning to successful handover into business-as-usual operations, with a focus on meeting project commitments on time as agreed with the customer, through strong teamwork and pragmatism.
Day to Day responsibility is to the Senior Programme Manager for the programme’s overall schedule;
Works as part of a matrix-team of multi-talented people from across geographical locations, cultures and organisations, including Vodafone, its vendors and its customers;
Analyse the project deliverables and manage cross-program dependencies to inform managers of schedule concerns, issues, and risks;
Analyse supplier (internal and third party) schedules and work with them to achieve against the approved baseline schedule;
Monitor governance standards across the portfolio, including tracking and updating project deliverables;
Creation and maintenance of project/program trackers, tools and documentation;
Assist with the preparation of consolidated material for project reports for regular review by key stakeholders;
Attend inter-department and customer meetings to facilitate communication of schedule changes and their impacts to various operating groups;
Oversee all communications within delivery groups WRT schedule compliance / deviation and managing the controls of schedule deviation (project change control);
Assist with the compilation and distribution of monthly portfolio level reports;
Use digital tools to enable decision making from Project/Program reports;
Support Project/Program Managers in the planning process;
Align schedule across workstreams for PM’s Low-Level Design and contractor resources, maintaining all inter-dependencies and resolving conflicts;
Provide admin support across the portfolio, including documentation control, meeting scheduling, minute taking and database maintenance;
Define and implement schedule change approval and tracking processes;
Collaborate with peers working in other portfolios to ensure best practice and lessons learned are being shared;
Promote the use of digital tools over manual processes and handoffs; and
Maintain customer standards to handle proposed project change.

Core competencies, Knowledge and experience
1. Previous experience
A successful track record of supporting complex customer projects within a fast-paced ICT or Telecommunications industry;
Experience of working in a highly matrixed, Agile organisation; and
Previous Project Co-ordinator experience required who has experienced with the project management lifecycle.
2. Tools
Strong digital skills across the whole O365 suite including PowerApps and PowerBI are desirable. MS Excel & MS Project knowledge is mandatory; and
Experience of using other project support tools; such as SharePoint & project management reporting tools (e.g. Planview/SAP).
3. Communication
Excellent interpersonal, organisational, communication and presentation skills, especially when working with remote team members and stakeholders;
Established team player with the ability to build strong relationships with customers, vendors and internal stakeholders;
A self-starter with a determination to succeed, balanced with appropriate tact and diplomacy; and
Ability to manage from a distance, resources who work for other organisations.
4. Languages & Soft skills
A dynamic approach to working in matrix teams, with a drive towards team empowerment and self-sufficiency;
Pragmatic approach to problem solving and issue resolution;
A keen interest in continuous improvement and digitisation; and
Good integrity, respect for confidentiality, sound judgment and decision-making skills.

Roles & Responsibilities
· Assists in the co-ordination of project management activities to ensure that projects are executed in a smooth and effective manner;
· Attends external project kick-off meetings, meetings with consultants as well as technical and co-ordination meetings, daily project meetings and internal project closure meeting;
· Assists in carrying out all shop drawings and submission with Drafting Department;
· Assists in carrying out risk assessment and other risk management activities; makes recommendations on risk control measures; communicating risk assessment to all workers;
· Ensures all contractors are safety inducted and issued with Permit before work commencement;
· Ensures the adherence to the safe work procedure (SWP) established; to inform project director of any shortcoming in the SWP or risk control measures implemented;
· Ensures the familiarization with the scope of works;
· Resolves site problems proactively in a timely manner
· Ensures the timely preparation of project progress and other reports;
· Follows up on all aspects of QA/QC matters; records all defects works and ensure proper documentation;
· Co-ordinates daily activities of workers’ duties and to ensure that they are performed in a proper manner;
· Makes daily checks on work progress, housekeeping and safety implementation on site with safety personnel;
· Assists in cost control by cutting materials wastage, reducing labour cost, usage of tools and equipment, etc;
· Assists in conducting Mass Tool Box meeting with safety personnel;
· Orders materials required for projects;
· Takes photographs on project progress and damage;
· Ensures proper project documentation including email communication;
· Issues work checklists for site supervisor;
· Initials and controls all delivery orders;
· Assists in promoting good team morale and team spirit in the project team;
· Any other duties as assigned.

